Task 1: Discover Network Assets with nmap
Step 1.1: Install and Configure nmap
# Update package repositories and install nmap
sudo apt update && sudo apt install -y nmap

# Verify installation
nmap --version

# Create working directory
mkdir ~/zero-trust-lab && cd ~/zero-trust-lab
Step 1.2: Perform Network Scans
Execute various nmap scans to discover assets and services:

# Basic host discovery scan
nmap -sn 127.0.0.1

# Comprehensive scan with service detection
nmap -sS -sV -p 1-1000 -oX localhost_scan.xml 127.0.0.1

# Scan with OS detection and default scripts
nmap -A -p 1-10000 --script=default -oX comprehensive_scan.xml 127.0.0.1

# Verify XML output files were created
ls -lh *.xml
Key nmap Options:

-sS: TCP SYN scan (stealth scan)
-sV: Service version detection
-A: Aggressive scan (OS detection, version detection, script scanning)
-oX: Output results in XML format
-p: Specify port range
Step 1.3: Review Scan Results
# View scan summary
cat comprehensive_scan.xml | grep -E "host|port|service" | head -20

# Check file sizes
du -h *.xml
