Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: Elasticsearch fails to start

Check Java installation: java -version
Verify sufficient memory: free -h
Check logs: sudo journalctl -u elasticsearch -n 50
Ensure port 9200 is not in use: sudo netstat -tlnp | grep 9200
Issue: Kibana cannot connect to Elasticsearch

Verify Elasticsearch is running: curl localhost:9200
Check Kibana configuration: cat /etc/kibana/kibana.yml
Review Kibana logs: sudo journalctl -u kibana -n 50
Issue: Python script fails to parse XML

Verify XML file exists and is not empty: ls -lh *.xml
Check XML syntax: xmllint --noout comprehensive_scan.xml
Ensure proper file permissions: chmod 644 *.xml
Issue: No data appears in Kibana

Verify data was uploaded: curl localhost:9200/zero-trust-assets/_count
Check index pattern matches index name
Refresh index pattern in Kibana
Verify time range in Kibana matches scan_time values
